Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%oz} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%oz} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While carrots roast, place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid; drain and return potatoes to pot. Mash with one packet sour cream and 1 TBSP @butter{2%tbsp} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Stir in half the scallion greens. Season with salt and pepper. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt and pepper.

Place 1 TBSP butter in a #shallow microwave-safe dish{}. Microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @Panko Breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, @Frank's RedHot® Original Seasoning Blend{0.24%oz}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Brush one packet @sour cream{1.5%tbsp} onto tops of chicken in a thin layer. Working one piece at a time, dip brushed sides of chicken into panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Place chicken, coated sides up, on a second, lightly oiled baking sheet.

Roast chicken on middle rack until browned and cooked through, ~{15-18%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{} to rest.

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Blue Cheese Dressing{1.5%oz}, scallion whites, and remaining sour cream.

Divide carrots, mashed potatoes, and chicken between plates. Top chicken with blue cheese sauce, remaining scallion greens, and @?Hot Sauce{1%tsp} if desired. Serve with any remaining blue cheese sauce on the side.